;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BHP@MNPM@?5Ahh?0?5the?5story?5of?5our?5King?0?5is?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BHP@MNPM@?5Ahh?0?5the?5story?5of?5our?5King?0?5is?5@ DB ' Ahh, the'
	DB	' story of our King, is it? The tragic fall of Leoric was a ha'
	DB	'rsh blow to this land. The people always loved the King, and '
	DB	'now they live in mortal fear of him. The question that I keep'
	DB	' asking myself is how he could have fallen so far from the Li'
	DB	'ght, as Leoric had always been the holiest of men. Only the v'
	DB	'ilest powers of Hell could so utterly destroy a man from with'
	DB	'in... |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0DOE@KIMK@The?5village?5needs?5your?5help?0?5goo@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0DOE@KIMK@The?5village?5needs?5your?5help?0?5goo@ DB 'The village n'
	DB	'eeds your help, good master! Some months ago King Leoric''s s'
	DB	'on, Prince Albrecht, was kidnapped. The King went into a rage'
	DB	' and scoured the village for his missing child. With each pas'
	DB	'sing day, Leoric seemed to slip deeper into madness. He sough'
	DB	't to blame innocent townsfolk for the boy''s disappearance an'
	DB	'd had them brutally executed. Less than half of us survived h'
	DB	'is insanity...', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'The King''s Knights and Prie'
	DB	'sts tried to placate him, but he turned against them and sadl'
	DB	'y, they were forced to kill him. With his dying breath the Ki'
	DB	'ng called down a terrible curse upon his former followers. He'
	DB	' vowed that they would serve him in darkness forever...', 0aH
	DB	' ', 0aH, 'This is where things take an even darker twist than'
	DB	' I thought possible! Our former King has risen from his etern'
	DB	'al sleep and now commands a legion of undead minions within t'
	DB	'he Labyrinth. His body was buried in a tomb three levels bene'
	DB	'ath the Cathedral. Please, good master, put his soul at ease '
	DB	'by destroying his now cursed form... |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JP@DHAN@As?5I?5told?5you?0?5good?5master?0?5the?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JP@DHAN@As?5I?5told?5you?0?5good?5master?0?5the?5@ DB 'As I told y'
	DB	'ou, good master, the King was entombed three levels below. He'
	DB	'''s down there, waiting in the putrid darkness for his chance'
	DB	' to destroy this land... |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0PG@FDPL@The?5curse?5of?5our?5King?5has?5passed@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0PG@FDPL@The?5curse?5of?5our?5King?5has?5passed@ DB 'The curse of o'
	DB	'ur King has passed, but I fear that it was only part of a gre'
	DB	'ater evil at work. However, we may yet be saved from the dark'
	DB	'ness that consumes our land, for your victory is a good omen.'
	DB	' May Light guide you on your way, good master. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBN@MEID@The?5loss?5of?5his?5son?5was?5too?5much@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBN@MEID@The?5loss?5of?5his?5son?5was?5too?5much@ DB 'The loss of '
	DB	'his son was too much for King Leoric. I did what I could to e'
	DB	'ase his madness, but in the end it overcame him. A black curs'
	DB	'e has hung over this kingdom from that day forward, but perha'
	DB	'ps if you were to free his spirit from his earthly prison, th'
	DB	'e curse would be lifted... |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
