_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0ENC@DIKO@This?5does?5not?5bode?5well?0?5for?5it?5@ DB 'This does n'
	DB	'ot bode well, for it confirms my darkest fears. While I did n'
	DB	'ot allow myself to believe the ancient legends, I cannot deny'
	DB	' them now. Perhaps the time has come to reveal who I am.', 0aH
	DB	' ', 0aH, 'My true name is Deckard Cain the Elder, and I am th'
	DB	'e last descendant of an ancient Brotherhood that was dedicate'
	DB	'd to safeguarding the secrets of a timeless evil. An evil tha'
	DB	't quite obviously has now been released.', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Th'
	DB	'e Archbishop Lazarus, once King Leoric''s most trusted adviso'
	DB	'r, led a party of simple townsfolk into the Labyrinth to find'
	DB	' the King''s missing son, Albrecht. Quite some time passed be'
	DB	'fore they returned, and only a few of them escaped with their'
	DB	' lives.', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Curse me for a fool! I should have '
	DB	'suspected his veiled treachery then. It must have been Lazaru'
	DB	's himself who kidnapped Albrecht and has since hidden him wit'
	DB	'hin the Labyrinth. I do not understand why the Archbishop tur'
	DB	'ned to the darkness, or what his interest is in the child. un'
	DB	'less he means to sacrifice him to his dark masters!', 0aH, ' '
	DB	0aH, 'That must be what he has planned! The survivors of his '''
	DB	'rescue party'' say that Lazarus was last seen running into th'
	DB	'e deepest bowels of the labyrinth. You must hurry and save th'
	DB	'e prince from the sacrificial blade of this demented fiend! |'
	DB	00H						; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0HP@JHAM@You?5must?5hurry?5and?5rescue?5Albrec@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0HP@JHAM@You?5must?5hurry?5and?5rescue?5Albrec@ DB 'You must hurry '
	DB	'and rescue Albrecht from the hands of Lazarus. The prince and'
	DB	' the people of this kingdom are counting on you! |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0CGP@BPPO@Your?5story?5is?5quite?5grim?0?5my?5fri@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0CGP@BPPO@Your?5story?5is?5quite?5grim?0?5my?5fri@ DB 'Your story i'
	DB	's quite grim, my friend. Lazarus will surely burn in Hell for'
	DB	' his horrific deed. The boy that you describe is not our prin'
	DB	'ce, but I believe that Albrecht may yet be in danger. The sym'
	DB	'bol of power that you speak of must be a portal in the very h'
	DB	'eart of the labyrinth.', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Know this, my friend'
	DB	' - The evil that you move against is the dark Lord of Terror.'
	DB	' He is known to mortal men as Diablo. It was he who was impri'
	DB	'soned within the Labyrinth many centuries ago and I fear that'
	DB	' he seeks to once again sow chaos in the realm of mankind. Yo'
	DB	'u must venture through the portal and destroy Diablo before i'
