_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BNM@DNCC@You?5claim?5to?5have?5spoken?5with?5La@ DB 'You claim to '
	DB	'have spoken with Lachdanan? He was a great hero during his li'
	DB	'fe. Lachdanan was an honorable and just man who served his Ki'
	DB	'ng faithfully for years. But of course, you already know that'
	DB	'.', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Of those who were caught within the grasp'
	DB	' of the King''s Curse, Lachdanan would be the least likely to'
	DB	' submit to the darkness without a fight, so I suppose that yo'
	DB	'ur story could be true. If I were in your place, my friend, I'
	DB	' would find a way to release him from his torture. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0IG@IJIF@You?5speak?5of?5a?5brave?5warrior?5lon@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0IG@IJIF@You?5speak?5of?5a?5brave?5warrior?5lon@ DB 'You speak of a'
	DB	' brave warrior long dead! I''ll have no such talk of speaking'
	DB	' with departed souls in my inn yard, thank you very much. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBE@FPLK@A?5golden?5elixir?0?5you?5say?4?5I?5have@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBE@FPLK@A?5golden?5elixir?0?5you?5say?4?5I?5have@ DB 'A golden el'
	DB	'ixir, you say. I have never concocted a potion of that color '
	DB	'before, so I can''t tell you how it would effect you if you w'
	DB	'ere to try to drink it. As your healer, I strongly advise tha'
	DB	't should you find such an elixir, do as Lachdanan asks and DO'
	DB	' NOT try to use it. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0GK@DADD@I?8ve?5never?5heard?5of?5a?5Lachdanan?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0GK@DADD@I?8ve?5never?5heard?5of?5a?5Lachdanan?5@ DB 'I''ve never h'
	DB	'eard of a Lachdanan before. I''m sorry, but I don''t think th'
	DB	'at I can be of much help to you. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAI@PBNB@If?5it?5is?5actually?5Lachdanan?5that@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAI@PBNB@If?5it?5is?5actually?5Lachdanan?5that@ DB 'If it is actua'
	DB	'lly Lachdanan that you have met, then I would advise that you'
	DB	' aid him. I dealt with him on several occasions and found him'
	DB	' to be honest and loyal in nature. The curse that fell upon t'
	DB	'he followers of King Leoric would fall especially hard upon h'
	DB	'im. |', 00H					; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0ID@CAPA@?5Lachdanan?5is?5dead?4?5Everybody?5kn@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0ID@CAPA@?5Lachdanan?5is?5dead?4?5Everybody?5kn@ DB ' Lachdanan is '
	DB	'dead. Everybody knows that, and you can''t fool me into think'
	DB	'ing any other way. You can''t talk to the dead. I know! |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JO@EHOM@You?5may?5meet?5people?5who?5are?5trap@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JO@EHOM@You?5may?5meet?5people?5who?5are?5trap@ DB 'You may meet p'
	DB	'eople who are trapped within the Labyrinth, such as Lachdanan'
	DB	'. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'I sense in him honor and great guilt. Ai'
	DB	'd him, and you aid all of Tristram. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAO@LAIB@Wait?0?5let?5me?5guess?4?5Cain?5was?5swa@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAO@LAIB@Wait?0?5let?5me?5guess?4?5Cain?5was?5swa@ DB 'Wait, let m'
	DB	'e guess. Cain was swallowed up in a gigantic fissure that ope'
	DB	'ned beneath him. He was incinerated in a ball of hellfire, an'
	DB	'd can''t answer your questions anymore. Oh, that isn''t what '
	DB	'happened? Then I guess you''ll be buying something or you''ll'
	DB	' be on your way. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0CJA@CGLA@Please?0?5don?8t?5kill?5me?0?5just?5hear@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0CJA@CGLA@Please?0?5don?8t?5kill?5me?0?5just?5hear@ DB 'Please, don'
	DB	'''t kill me, just hear me out. I was once Captain of King Leo'
	DB	'ric''s Knights, upholding the laws of this land with justice '
	DB	'and honor. Then his dark Curse fell upon us for the role we p'
	DB	'layed in his tragic death. As my fellow Knights succumbed to '
	DB	'their twisted fate, I fled from the King''s burial chamber, s'
	DB	'earching for some way to free myself from the Curse. I failed'
	DB	'...', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'I have heard of a Golden Elixir that co'
	DB	'uld lift the Curse and allow my soul to rest, but I have been'
	DB	' unable to find it. My strength now wanes, and with it the la'
	DB	'st of my humanity as well. Please aid me and find the Elixir.'
	DB	' I will repay your efforts - I swear upon my honor. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0GF@KDAC@You?5have?5not?5found?5the?5Golden?5El@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0GF@KDAC@You?5have?5not?5found?5the?5Golden?5El@ DB 'You have not f'
	DB	'ound the Golden Elixir. I fear that I am doomed for eternity.'
	DB	' Please, keep trying... |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BEK@GDGJ@You?5have?5saved?5my?5soul?5from?5damn@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BEK@GDGJ@You?5have?5saved?5my?5soul?5from?5damn@ DB 'You have save'
	DB	'd my soul from damnation, and for that I am in your debt. If '
	DB	'there is ever a way that I can repay you from beyond the grav'
	DB	'e I will find it, but for now - take my helm. On the journey '
	DB	'I am about to take I will have little use for it. May it prot'
	DB	'ect you against the dark powers below. Go with the Light, my '
	DB	'friend... |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0CBG@BNMH@Griswold?5speaks?5of?5The?5Anvil?5of?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0CBG@BNMH@Griswold?5speaks?5of?5The?5Anvil?5of?5@ DB 'Griswold spea'
	DB	'ks of The Anvil of Fury - a legendary artifact long searched '
	DB	'for, but never found. Crafted from the metallic bones of the '
	DB	'Razor Pit demons, the Anvil of Fury was smelt around the skul'
	DB	'ls of the five most powerful magi of the underworld. Carved w'
	DB	'ith runes of power and chaos, any weapon or armor forged upon'
	DB	' this Anvil will be immersed into the realm of Chaos, imbeddi'
	DB	'ng it with magical properties. It is said that the unpredicta'
	DB	'ble nature of Chaos makes it difficult to know what the outco'
	DB	'me of this smithing will be... |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0GI@PFKF@Don?8t?5you?5think?5that?5Griswold?5wo@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0GI@PFKF@Don?8t?5you?5think?5that?5Griswold?5wo@ DB 'Don''t you thi'
	DB	'nk that Griswold would be a better person to ask about this? '
	DB	'He''s quite handy, you know. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0OI@NGGI@If?5you?5had?5been?5looking?5for?5info@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0OI@NGGI@If?5you?5had?5been?5looking?5for?5info@ DB 'If you had bee'
	DB	'n looking for information on the Pestle of Curing or the Silv'
	DB	'er Chalice of Purification, I could have assisted you, my fri'
	DB	'end. However, in this matter, you would be better served to s'
	DB	'peak to either Griswold or Cain. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBH@BOEP@Griswold?8s?5father?5used?5to?5tell?5s@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBH@BOEP@Griswold?8s?5father?5used?5to?5tell?5s@ DB 'Griswold''s f'
	DB	'ather used to tell some of us when we were growing up about a'
	DB	' giant anvil that was used to make mighty weapons. He said th'
	DB	'at when a hammer was struck upon this anvil, the ground would'
	DB	' shake with a great fury. Whenever the earth moves, I always '
	DB	'remember that story. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0DHE@GKGO@Greetings?$CB?5It?8s?5always?5a?5pleasur@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0DHE@GKGO@Greetings?$CB?5It?8s?5always?5a?5pleasur@ DB 'Greetings! '
	DB	'It''s always a pleasure to see one of my best customers! I kn'
	DB	'ow that you have been venturing deeper into the Labyrinth, an'
	DB	'd there is a story I was told that you may find worth the tim'
	DB	'e to listen to...', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'One of the men who return'
	DB	'ed from the Labyrinth told me about a mystic anvil that he ca'
	DB	'me across during his escape. His description reminded me of l'
	DB	'egends I had heard in my youth about the burning Hellforge wh'
	DB	'ere powerful weapons of magic are crafted. The legend had it '
	DB	'that deep within the Hellforge rested the Anvil of Fury! This'
	DB	' Anvil contained within it the very essence of the demonic un'
	DB	'derworld...', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'It is said that any weapon craf'
	DB	'ted upon the burning Anvil is imbued with great power. If thi'
	DB	's anvil is indeed the Anvil of Fury, I may be able to make yo'
	DB	'u a weapon capable of defeating even the darkest lord of Hell'
	DB	'! ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Find the Anvil for me, and I''ll get to '
	DB	'work! |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0KB@BMCB@Nothing?5yet?0?5eh?$DP?5Well?0?5keep?5sear@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0KB@BMCB@Nothing?5yet?0?5eh?$DP?5Well?0?5keep?5sear@ DB 'Nothing ye'
	DB	't, eh? Well, keep searching. A weapon forged upon the Anvil c'
	DB	'ould be your best hope, and I am sure that I can make you one'
	DB	' of legendary proportions. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0NG@BKNC@I?5can?5hardly?5believe?5it?$CB?5This?5is@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0NG@BKNC@I?5can?5hardly?5believe?5it?$CB?5This?5is@ DB 'I can hardl'
	DB	'y believe it! This is the Anvil of Fury - good work, my frien'
	DB	'd. Now we''ll show those bastards that there are no weapons i'
	DB	'n Hell more deadly than those made by men! Take this and may '
	DB	'Light protect you. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0GG@KIBD@Griswold?5can?8t?5sell?5his?5anvil?4?5W@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0GG@KIBD@Griswold?5can?8t?5sell?5his?5anvil?4?5W@ DB 'Griswold can'''
	DB	't sell his anvil. What will he do then? And I''d be angry too'
	DB	' if someone took my anvil! |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBG@FNHD@There?5are?5many?5artifacts?5within?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBG@FNHD@There?5are?5many?5artifacts?5within?5@ DB 'There are many'
	DB	' artifacts within the Labyrinth that hold powers beyond the c'
	DB	'omprehension of mortals. Some of these hold fantastic power t'
	DB	'hat can be used by either the Light or the Darkness. Securing'
	DB	' the Anvil from below could shift the course of the Sin War t'
	DB	'owards the Light. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0IC@MEGF@If?5you?5were?5to?5find?5this?5artifac@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0IC@MEGF@If?5you?5were?5to?5find?5this?5artifac@ DB 'If you were to'
	DB	' find this artifact for Griswold, it could put a serious damp'
	DB	'er on my business here. Awwww, you''ll never find it. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0DGD@CLHN@The?5Gateway?5of?5Blood?5and?5the?5Hal@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0DGD@CLHN@The?5Gateway?5of?5Blood?5and?5the?5Hal@ DB 'The Gateway o'
	DB	'f Blood and the Halls of Fire are landmarks of mystic origin.'
	DB	' Wherever this book you read from resides it is surely a plac'
	DB	'e of great power.', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Legends speak of a pedest'
	DB	'al that is carved from obsidian stone and has a pool of boili'
	DB	'ng blood atop its bone encrusted surface. There are also allu'
	DB	'sions to Stones of Blood that will open a door that guards an'
	DB	' ancient treasure...', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'The nature of this tre'
	DB	'asure is shrouded in speculation, my friend, but it is said t'
	DB	'hat the ancient hero Arkaine placed the holy armor Valor in a'
	DB	' secret vault. Arkaine was the first mortal to turn the tide '
	DB	'of the Sin War and chase the legions of darkness back to the '
	DB	'Burning Hells.', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Just before Arkaine died, hi'
	DB	's armor was hidden away in a secret vault. It is said that wh'
	DB	'en this holy armor is again needed, a hero will arise to don '
	DB	'Valor once more. Perhaps you are that hero... |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0LO@MLKC@Every?5child?5hears?5the?5story?5of?5t@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0LO@MLKC@Every?5child?5hears?5the?5story?5of?5t@ DB 'Every child he'
	DB	'ars the story of the warrior Arkaine and his mystic armor kno'
	DB	'wn as Valor. If you could find its resting place, you would b'
	DB	'e well protected against the evil in the Labyrinth. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JP@BOGN@Hmm?4?4?4?5it?5sounds?5like?5something?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JP@BOGN@Hmm?4?4?4?5it?5sounds?5like?5something?5@ DB 'Hmm... it so'
	DB	'unds like something I should remember, but I''ve been so busy'
	DB	' learning new cures and creating better elixirs that I must h'
	DB	'ave forgotten. Sorry... |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0IO@FJEP@The?5story?5of?5the?5magic?5armor?5cal@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0IO@FJEP@The?5story?5of?5the?5magic?5armor?5cal@ DB 'The story of t'
	DB	'he magic armor called Valor is something I often heard the bo'
	DB	'ys talk about. You had better ask one of the men in the villa'
	DB	'ge. |', 00H					; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBN@BIHB@The?5armor?5known?5as?5Valor?5could?5b@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBN@BIHB@The?5armor?5known?5as?5Valor?5could?5b@ DB 'The armor kno'
	DB	'wn as Valor could be what tips the scales in your favor. I wi'
	DB	'll tell you that many have looked for it - including myself. '
	DB	'Arkaine hid it well, my friend, and it will take more than a '
	DB	'bit of luck to unlock the secrets that have kept it concealed'
	DB	' oh, lo these many years. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0CG@DHDB@Zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0CG@DHDB@Zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz@ DB 'Zzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzzz'
	DB	'zzzzzzzzzzzz... |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JA@LPJL@Should?5you?5find?5these?5Stones?5of?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JA@LPJL@Should?5you?5find?5these?5Stones?5of?5@ DB 'Should you fin'
	DB	'd these Stones of Blood, use them carefully. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH
	DB	'The way is fraught with danger and your only hope rests withi'
	DB	'n your self trust. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0LM@ONEI@You?5intend?5to?5find?5the?5armor?5kno@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0LM@ONEI@You?5intend?5to?5find?5the?5armor?5kno@ DB 'You intend to '
	DB	'find the armor known as Valor? ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'No one has '
	DB	'ever figured out where Arkaine stashed the stuff, and if my c'
	DB	'ontacts couldn''t find it, I seriously doubt you ever will ei'
	DB	'ther. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0CDK@LJNG@I?5know?5of?5only?5one?5legend?5that?5s@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0CDK@LJNG@I?5know?5of?5only?5one?5legend?5that?5s@ DB 'I know of on'
	DB	'ly one legend that speaks of such a warrior as you describe. '
	DB	'His story is found within the ancient chronicles of the Sin W'
	DB	'ar...', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Stained by a thousand years of war, b'
	DB	'lood and death, the Warlord of Blood stands upon a mountain o'
	DB	'f his tattered victims. His dark blade screams a black curse '
	DB	'to the living; a tortured invitation to any who would stand b'
	DB	'efore this Executioner of Hell.', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'It is also '
	DB	'written that although he was once a mortal who fought beside '
	DB	'the Legion of Darkness during the Sin War, he lost his humani'
	DB	'ty to his insatiable hunger for blood. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0KE@EBNB@I?5am?5afraid?5that?5I?5haven?8t?5heard@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0KE@EBNB@I?5am?5afraid?5that?5I?5haven?8t?5heard@ DB 'I am afraid t'
	DB	'hat I haven''t heard anything about such a vicious warrior, g'
	DB	'ood master. I hope that you do not have to fight him, for he '
	DB	'sounds extremely dangerous. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0GF@BICG@Cain?5would?5be?5able?5to?5tell?5you?5m@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0GF@BICG@Cain?5would?5be?5able?5to?5tell?5you?5m@ DB 'Cain would be'
	DB	' able to tell you much more about something like this than I '
	DB	'would ever wish to know. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0HK@JAMK@If?5you?5are?5to?5battle?5such?5a?5fier@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0HK@JAMK@If?5you?5are?5to?5battle?5such?5a?5fier@ DB 'If you are to'
	DB	' battle such a fierce opponent, may Light be your guide and y'
	DB	'our defender. I will keep you in my thoughts. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0HN@MICE@Dark?5and?5wicked?5legends?5surround@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0HN@MICE@Dark?5and?5wicked?5legends?5surround@ DB 'Dark and wicked '
	DB	'legends surrounds the one Warlord of Blood. Be well prepared,'
	DB	' my friend, for he shows no mercy or quarter. |', 00H ; `string'
