_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BLA@CMEH@The?5story?5of?5Wirt?5is?5a?5frighteni@ DB 'The story of '
	DB	'Wirt is a frightening and tragic one. He was taken from the a'
	DB	'rms of his mother and dragged into the labyrinth by the small'
	DB	', foul demons that wield wicked spears. There were many other'
	DB	' children taken that day, including the son of King Leoric. T'
	DB	'he Knights of the palace went below, but never returned. The '
	DB	'Blacksmith found the boy, but only after the foul beasts had '
	DB	'begun to torture him for their sadistic pleasures. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0ON@LHIM@Ah?0?5Pepin?4?5I?5count?5him?5as?5a?5true@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0ON@LHIM@Ah?0?5Pepin?4?5I?5count?5him?5as?5a?5true@ DB 'Ah, Pepin. '
	DB	'I count him as a true friend - perhaps the closest I have her'
	DB	'e. He is a bit addled at times, but never a more caring or co'
	DB	'nsiderate soul has existed. His knowledge and skills are equa'
	DB	'led by few, and his door is always open. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BDP@IHNJ@Gillian?5is?5a?5fine?5woman?4?5Much?5ad@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BDP@IHNJ@Gillian?5is?5a?5fine?5woman?4?5Much?5ad@ DB 'Gillian is a'
	DB	' fine woman. Much adored for her high spirits and her quick l'
	DB	'augh, she holds a special place in my heart. She stays on at '
	DB	'the tavern to support her elderly grandmother who is too sick'
	DB	' to travel. I sometimes fear for her safety, but I know that '
	DB	'any man in the village would rather die than see her harmed. '
	DB	'|', 00H					; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0ED@IHED@Greetings?0?5good?5master?4?5Welcome?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0ED@IHED@Greetings?0?5good?5master?4?5Welcome?5@ DB 'Greetings, goo'
	DB	'd master. Welcome to the Tavern of the Rising Sun! |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAP@KJPC@Many?5adventurers?5have?5graced?5the@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAP@KJPC@Many?5adventurers?5have?5graced?5the@ DB 'Many adventurer'
	DB	's have graced the tables of my tavern, and ten times as many '
	DB	'stories have been told over as much ale. The only thing that '
	DB	'I ever heard any of them agree on was this old axiom. Perhaps'
	DB	' it will help you. You can cut the flesh, but you must crush '
	DB	'the bone. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JI@NDOI@Griswold?5the?5blacksmith?5is?5extre@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JI@NDOI@Griswold?5the?5blacksmith?5is?5extre@ DB 'Griswold the bla'
	DB	'cksmith is extremely knowledgeable about weapons and armor. I'
	DB	'f you ever need work done on your gear, he is definitely the '
	DB	'man to see. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JL@LFFN@Farnham?5spends?5far?5too?5much?5time@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JL@LFFN@Farnham?5spends?5far?5too?5much?5time@ DB 'Farnham spends '
	DB	'far too much time here, drowning his sorrows in cheap ale. I '
	DB	'would make him leave, but he did suffer so during his time in'
	DB	' the Labyrinth. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0NK@CCDK@Adria?5is?5wise?5beyond?5her?5years?0?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0NK@CCDK@Adria?5is?5wise?5beyond?5her?5years?0?5@ DB 'Adria is wise'
	DB	' beyond her years, but I must admit - she frightens me a litt'
	DB	'le. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Well, no matter. If you ever have need'
	DB	' to trade in items of sorcery, she maintains a strangely well'
	DB	'-stocked hut just across the river. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0HE@GCOP@If?5you?5want?5to?5know?5more?5about?5t@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0HE@GCOP@If?5you?5want?5to?5know?5more?5about?5t@ DB 'If you want t'
	DB	'o know more about the history of our village, the storyteller'
	DB	' Cain knows quite a bit about the past. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAP@GJPF@Wirt?5is?5a?5rapscallion?5and?5a?5litt@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAP@GJPF@Wirt?5is?5a?5rapscallion?5and?5a?5litt@ DB 'Wirt is a rap'
	DB	'scallion and a little scoundrel. He was always getting into t'
	DB	'rouble, and it''s no surprise what happened to him. ', 0aH, ' '
	DB	0aH, 'He probably went fooling about someplace that he shouldn'
	DB	'''t have been. I feel sorry for the boy, but I don''t abide t'
	DB	'he company that he keeps. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0MH@GOFJ@Pepin?5is?5a?5good?5man?5?9?5and?5certai@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0MH@GOFJ@Pepin?5is?5a?5good?5man?5?9?5and?5certai@ DB 'Pepin is a g'
	DB	'ood man - and certainly the most generous in the village. He '
	DB	'is always attending to the needs of others, but trouble of so'
	DB	'me sort or another does seem to follow him wherever he goes..'
	DB	'. |', 00H					; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAE@GCN@Gillian?0?5my?5Barmaid?$DP?5If?5it?5were?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAE@GCN@Gillian?0?5my?5Barmaid?$DP?5If?5it?5were?5@ DB 'Gillian, m'
	DB	'y Barmaid? If it were not for her sense of duty to her grand-'
	DB	'dam, she would have fled from here long ago. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH
	DB	'Goodness knows I begged her to leave, telling her that I woul'
	DB	'd watch after the old woman, but she is too sweet and caring '
	DB	'to have done so. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BM@OKLI@What?5ails?5you?0?5my?5friend?$DP?5?$HM?$AA@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BM@OKLI@What?5ails?5you?0?5my?5friend?$DP?5?$HM?$AA@ DB 'What ails'
	DB	' you, my friend? |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0OM@CINH@I?5have?5made?5a?5very?5interesting?5d@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0OM@CINH@I?5have?5made?5a?5very?5interesting?5d@ DB 'I have made a '
	DB	'very interesting discovery. Unlike us, the creatures in the L'
	DB	'abyrinth can heal themselves without the aid of potions or ma'
	DB	'gic. If you hurt one of the monsters, make sure it is dead or'
	DB	' it very well may regenerate itself. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0PH@OFIE@Before?5it?5was?5taken?5over?5by?0?5wel@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0PH@OFIE@Before?5it?5was?5taken?5over?5by?0?5wel@ DB 'Before it was'
	DB	' taken over by, well, whatever lurks below, the Cathedral was'
	DB	' a place of great learning. There are many books to be found '
	DB	'there. If you find any, you should read them all, for some ma'
	DB	'y hold secrets to the workings of the Labyrinth. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0NA@HMAC@Griswold?5knows?5as?5much?5about?5the@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0NA@HMAC@Griswold?5knows?5as?5much?5about?5the@ DB 'Griswold knows '
	DB	'as much about the art of war as I do about the art of healing'
	DB	'. He is a shrewd merchant, but his work is second to none. Oh'
	DB	', I suppose that may be because he is the only blacksmith lef'
	DB	't here. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0MF@KAKG@Cain?5is?5a?5true?5friend?5and?5a?5wise@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0MF@KAKG@Cain?5is?5a?5true?5friend?5and?5a?5wise@ DB 'Cain is a tru'
	DB	'e friend and a wise sage. He maintains a vast library and has'
	DB	' an innate ability to discern the true nature of many things.'
	DB	' If you ever have any questions, he is the person to go to. |'
	DB	00H						; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JG@MLH@Even?5my?5skills?5have?5been?5unable?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JG@MLH@Even?5my?5skills?5have?5been?5unable?5@ DB 'Even my skills '
	DB	'have been unable to fully heal Farnham. Oh, I have been able '
	DB	'to mend his body, but his mind and spirit are beyond anything'
	DB	' I can do. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BDP@CFOJ@While?5I?5use?5some?5limited?5forms?5o@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BDP@CFOJ@While?5I?5use?5some?5limited?5forms?5o@ DB 'While I use s'
	DB	'ome limited forms of magic to create the potions and elixirs '
	DB	'I store here, Adria is a true sorceress. She never seems to s'
	DB	'leep, and she always has access to many mystic tomes and arti'
	DB	'facts. I believe her hut may be much more than the hovel it a'
	DB	'ppears to be, but I can never seem to get inside the place. |'
	DB	00H						; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0PD@HPPJ@Poor?5Wirt?4?5I?5did?5all?5that?5was?5po@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0PD@HPPJ@Poor?5Wirt?4?5I?5did?5all?5that?5was?5po@ DB 'Poor Wirt. I'
	DB	' did all that was possible for the child, but I know he despi'
	DB	'ses that wooden peg that I was forced to attach to his leg. H'
	DB	'is wounds were hideous. No one - and especially such a young '
	DB	'child - should have to suffer the way he did. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BGM@GGCO@I?5really?5don?8t?5understand?5why?5Og@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BGM@GGCO@I?5really?5don?8t?5understand?5why?5Og@ DB 'I really don'''
	DB	't understand why Ogden stays here in Tristram. He suffers fro'
	DB	'm a slight nervous condition, but he is an intelligent and in'
	DB	'dustrious man who would do very well wherever he went. I supp'
	DB	'ose it may be the fear of the many murders that happen in the'
	DB	' surrounding countryside, or perhaps the wishes of his wife t'
	DB	'hat keep him and his family where they are. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0LE@CPOG@Ogden?8s?5barmaid?5is?5a?5sweet?5girl?4@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0LE@CPOG@Ogden?8s?5barmaid?5is?5a?5sweet?5girl?4@ DB 'Ogden''s barm'
	DB	'aid is a sweet girl. Her grandmother is quite ill, and suffer'
	DB	's from delusions. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'She claims that they are'
	DB	' visions, but I have no proof of that one way or the other. |'
	DB	00H						; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0CB@OAIK@Good?5day?$CB?5How?5may?5I?5serve?5you?$DP?5?$HM@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0CB@OAIK@Good?5day?$CB?5How?5may?5I?5serve?5you?$DP?5?$HM@ DB 'Good'
	DB	' day! How may I serve you? |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0HI@CIIL@My?5grandmother?5had?5a?5dream?5that?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0HI@CIIL@My?5grandmother?5had?5a?5dream?5that?5@ DB 'My grandmother'
	DB	' had a dream that you would come and talk to me. She has visi'
	DB	'ons, you know and can see into the future. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0OG@PFKL@The?5woman?5at?5the?5edge?5of?5town?5is@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0OG@PFKL@The?5woman?5at?5the?5edge?5of?5town?5is@ DB 'The woman at '
	DB	'the edge of town is a witch! She seems nice enough, and her n'
	DB	'ame, Adria, is very pleasing to the ear, but I am very afraid'
	DB	' of her. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'It would take someone quite brave'
	DB	', like you, to see what she is doing out there. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAP@PJLN@Our?5Blacksmith?5is?5a?5point?5of?5pri@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAP@PJLN@Our?5Blacksmith?5is?5a?5point?5of?5pri@ DB 'Our Blacksmit'
	DB	'h is a point of pride to the people of Tristram. Not only is '
	DB	'he a master craftsman who has won many contests within his gu'
	DB	'ild, but he received praises from our King Leoric himself - m'
	DB	'ay his soul rest in peace. Griswold is also a great hero; jus'
	DB	't ask Cain. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JL@NENK@Cain?5has?5been?5the?5storyteller?5of@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JL@NENK@Cain?5has?5been?5the?5storyteller?5of@ DB 'Cain has been t'
	DB	'he storyteller of Tristram for as long as I can remember. He '
	DB	'knows so much, and can tell you just about anything about alm'
	DB	'ost everything. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0PL@GEFO@Farnham?5is?5a?5drunkard?5who?5fills?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0PL@GEFO@Farnham?5is?5a?5drunkard?5who?5fills?5@ DB 'Farnham is a d'
	DB	'runkard who fills his belly with ale and everyone else''s ear'
	DB	's with nonsense. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'I know that both Pepin an'
	DB	'd Ogden feel sympathy for him, but I get so frustrated watchi'
	DB	'ng him slip farther and farther into a befuddled stupor every'
	DB	' night. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAJ@GNCE@Pepin?5saved?5my?5grandmother?8s?5lif@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAJ@GNCE@Pepin?5saved?5my?5grandmother?8s?5lif@ DB 'Pepin saved my'
	DB	' grandmother''s life, and I know that I can never repay him f'
	DB	'or that. His ability to heal any sickness is more powerful th'
	DB	'an the mightiest sword and more mysterious than any spell you'
	DB	' can name. If you ever are in need of healing, Pepin can help'
	DB	' you. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BIC@BAOL@I?5grew?5up?5with?5Wirt?8s?5mother?0?5Ca@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BIC@BAOL@I?5grew?5up?5with?5Wirt?8s?5mother?0?5Ca@ DB 'I grew up w'
	DB	'ith Wirt''s mother, Canace. Although she was only slightly hu'
	DB	'rt when those hideous creatures stole him, she never recovere'
	DB	'd. I think she died of a broken heart. Wirt has become a mean'
	DB	'-spirited youngster, looking only to profit from the sweat of'
	DB	' others. I know that he suffered and has seen horrors that I '
	DB	'cannot even imagine, but some of that darkness hangs over him'
	DB	' still. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0PE@LNAL@Ogden?5and?5his?5wife?5have?5taken?5me@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0PE@LNAL@Ogden?5and?5his?5wife?5have?5taken?5me@ DB 'Ogden and his '
	DB	'wife have taken me and my grandmother into their home and hav'
	DB	'e even let me earn a few gold pieces by working at the inn. I'
	DB	' owe so much to them, and hope one day to leave this place an'
	DB	'd help them start a grand hotel in the east. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BO@IOHP@Well?0?5what?5can?5I?5do?5for?5ya?$DP?5?$HM?$AA@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BO@IOHP@Well?0?5what?5can?5I?5do?5for?5ya?$DP?5?$HM?$AA@ DB 'Well,'
	DB	' what can I do for ya? |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0PC@IMH@If?5you?8re?5looking?5for?5a?5good?5wea@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0PC@IMH@If?5you?8re?5looking?5for?5a?5good?5wea@ DB 'If you''re loo'
	DB	'king for a good weapon, let me show this to you. Take your ba'
	DB	'sic blunt weapon, such as a mace. Works like a charm against '
	DB	'most of those undying horrors down there, and there''s nothin'
	DB	'g better to shatter skinny little skeletons! |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0OI@IPDF@The?5axe?$DP?5Aye?0?5that?8s?5a?5good?5weap@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0OI@IPDF@The?5axe?$DP?5Aye?0?5that?8s?5a?5good?5weap@ DB 'The axe? '
	DB	'Aye, that''s a good weapon, balanced against any foe. Look ho'
	DB	'w it cleaves the air, and then imagine a nice fat demon head '
	DB	'in its path. Keep in mind, however, that it is slow to swing '
	DB	'- but talk about dealing a heavy blow! |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAD@LLLB@Look?5at?5that?5edge?0?5that?5balance?4@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAD@LLLB@Look?5at?5that?5edge?0?5that?5balance?4@ DB 'Look at that'
	DB	' edge, that balance. A sword in the right hands, and against '
	DB	'the right foe, is the master of all weapons. Its keen blade f'
	DB	'inds little to hack or pierce on the undead, but against a li'
	DB	'ving, breathing enemy, a sword will better slice their flesh!'
	DB	' |', 00H					; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0LL@JBEI@Your?5weapons?5and?5armor?5will?5show@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0LL@JBEI@Your?5weapons?5and?5armor?5will?5show@ DB 'Your weapons an'
	DB	'd armor will show the signs of your struggles against the Dar'
	DB	'kness. If you bring them to me, with a bit of work and a hot '
	DB	'forge, I can restore them to top fighting form. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BCJ@EEGB@While?5I?5have?5to?5practically?5smug@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BCJ@EEGB@While?5I?5have?5to?5practically?5smug@ DB 'While I have t'
	DB	'o practically smuggle in the metals and tools I need from car'
	DB	'avans that skirt the edges of our damned town, that witch, Ad'
	DB	'ria, always seems to get whatever she needs. If I knew even t'
	DB	'he smallest bit about how to harness magic as she did, I coul'
	DB	'd make some truly incredible things. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0JK@NIIE@Gillian?5is?5a?5nice?5lass?4?5Shame?5th@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0JK@NIIE@Gillian?5is?5a?5nice?5lass?4?5Shame?5th@ DB 'Gillian is a '
	DB	'nice lass. Shame that her gammer is in such poor health or I '
	DB	'would arrange to get both of them out of here on one of the t'
	DB	'rading caravans. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0MN@MBCF@Sometimes?5I?5think?5that?5Cain?5talk@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0MN@MBCF@Sometimes?5I?5think?5that?5Cain?5talk@ DB 'Sometimes I thi'
	DB	'nk that Cain talks too much, but I guess that is his calling '
	DB	'in life. If I could bend steel as well as he can bend your ea'
	DB	'r, I could make a suit of court plate good enough for an Empe'
	DB	'ror! |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BDA@BFLB@I?5was?5with?5Farnham?5that?5night?5th@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BDA@BFLB@I?5was?5with?5Farnham?5that?5night?5th@ DB 'I was with Fa'
	DB	'rnham that night that Lazarus led us into Labyrinth. I never '
	DB	'saw the Archbishop again, and I may not have survived if Farn'
	DB	'ham was not at my side. I fear that the attack left his soul '
	DB	'as crippled as, well, another did my leg. I cannot fight this'
	DB	' battle for him now, but I would if I could. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0LC@HEN@A?5good?5man?5who?5puts?5the?5needs?5of@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0LC@HEN@A?5good?5man?5who?5puts?5the?5needs?5of@ DB 'A good man who'
	DB	' puts the needs of others above his own. You won''t find anyo'
	DB	'ne left in Tristram - or anywhere else for that matter - who '
	DB	'has a bad thing to say about the healer. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BFC@GLJH@That?5lad?5is?5going?5to?5get?5himself@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BFC@GLJH@That?5lad?5is?5going?5to?5get?5himself@ DB 'That lad is g'
	DB	'oing to get himself into serious trouble... or I guess I shou'
	DB	'ld say, again. I''ve tried to interest him in working here an'
	DB	'd learning an honest trade, but he prefers the high profits o'
	DB	'f dealing in goods of dubious origin. I cannot hold that agai'
	DB	'nst him after what happened to him, but I do wish he would at'
	DB	' least be careful. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BMA@CFMJ@The?5Innkeeper?5has?5little?5busines@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BMA@CFMJ@The?5Innkeeper?5has?5little?5busines@ DB 'The Innkeeper h'
	DB	'as little business and no real way of turning a profit. He ma'
	DB	'nages to make ends meet by providing food and lodging for tho'
	DB	'se who occasionally drift through the village, but they are a'
	DB	's likely to sneak off into the night as they are to pay him. '
	DB	'If it weren''t for the stores of grains and dried meats he ke'
	DB	'pt in his cellar, why, most of us would have starved during t'
	DB	'hat first year when the entire countryside was overrun by dem'
	DB	'ons. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
