;	COMDAT ??_C@_0NN@NKBO@Wisdom?5is?5earned?0?5not?5given?4?5If?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0NN@NKBO@Wisdom?5is?5earned?0?5not?5given?4?5If?5@ DB 'Wisdom is ea'
	DB	'rned, not given. If you discover a tome of knowledge, devour '
	DB	'its words. Should you already have knowledge of the arcane my'
	DB	'steries scribed within a book, remember - that level of maste'
	DB	'ry can always increase. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BJK@COGJ@The?5greatest?5power?5is?5often?5the?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BJK@COGJ@The?5greatest?5power?5is?5often?5the?5@ DB 'The greatest '
	DB	'power is often the shortest lived. You may find ancient words'
	DB	' of power written upon scrolls of parchment. The strength of '
	DB	'these scrolls lies in the ability of either apprentice or ade'
	DB	'pt to cast them with equal ability. Their weakness is that th'
	DB	'ey must first be read aloud and can never be kept at the read'
	DB	'y in your mind. Know also that these scrolls can be read but '
	DB	'once, so use them with care. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BFO@DMBJ@Though?5the?5heat?5of?5the?5sun?5is?5be@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BFO@DMBJ@Though?5the?5heat?5of?5the?5sun?5is?5be@ DB 'Though the h'
	DB	'eat of the sun is beyond measure, the mere flame of a candle '
	DB	'is of greater danger. No energies, no matter how great, can b'
	DB	'e used without the proper focus. For many spells, ensorcelled'
	DB	' Staves may be charged with magical energies many times over.'
	DB	' I have the ability to restore their power - but know that no'
	DB	'thing is done without a price. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0MK@CCCJ@The?5sum?5of?5our?5knowledge?5is?5in?5t@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0MK@CCCJ@The?5sum?5of?5our?5knowledge?5is?5in?5t@ DB 'The sum of ou'
	DB	'r knowledge is in the sum of its people. Should you find a bo'
	DB	'ok or scroll that you cannot decipher, do not hesitate to bri'
	DB	'ng it to me. If I can make sense of it I will share what I fi'
	DB	'nd. |', 00H					; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0MB@NOML@To?5a?5man?5who?5only?5knows?5Iron?0?5th@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0MB@NOML@To?5a?5man?5who?5only?5knows?5Iron?0?5th@ DB 'To a man who'
	DB	' only knows Iron, there is no greater magic than Steel. The b'
	DB	'lacksmith Griswold is more of a sorcerer than he knows. His a'
	DB	'bility to meld fire and metal is unequaled in this land. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0OO@INKM@Corruption?5has?5the?5strength?5of?5d@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0OO@INKM@Corruption?5has?5the?5strength?5of?5d@ DB 'Corruption has '
	DB	'the strength of deceit, but innocence holds the power of puri'
	DB	'ty. The young woman Gillian has a pure heart, placing the nee'
	DB	'ds of her matriarch over her own. She fears me, but it is onl'
	DB	'y because she does not understand me. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAK@MNNG@A?5chest?5opened?5in?5darkness?5holds@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAK@MNNG@A?5chest?5opened?5in?5darkness?5holds@ DB 'A chest opened'
	DB	' in darkness holds no greater treasure than when it is opened'
	DB	' in the light. The storyteller Cain is an enigma, but only to'
	DB	' those who do not look. His knowledge of what lies beneath th'
	DB	'e cathedral is far greater than even he allows himself to rea'
	DB	'lize. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBH@CNBM@The?5higher?5you?5place?5your?5faith?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBH@CNBM@The?5higher?5you?5place?5your?5faith?5@ DB 'The higher yo'
	DB	'u place your faith in one man, the farther it has to fall. Fa'
	DB	'rnham has lost his soul, but not to any demon. It was lost wh'
	DB	'en he saw his fellow townspeople betrayed by the Archbishop L'
	DB	'azarus. He has knowledge to be gleaned, but you must separate'
	DB	' fact from fantasy. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BEB@BIKJ@The?5hand?0?5the?5heart?5and?5the?5mind@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BEB@BIKJ@The?5hand?0?5the?5heart?5and?5the?5mind@ DB 'The hand, th'
	DB	'e heart and the mind can perform miracles when they are in pe'
	DB	'rfect harmony. The healer Pepin sees into the body in a way t'
	DB	'hat even I cannot. His ability to restore the sick and injure'
	DB	'd is magnified by his understanding of the creation of elixir'
	DB	's and potions. He is as great an ally as you have in Tristram'
	DB	'. |', 00H					; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BMP@FECG@There?5is?5much?5about?5the?5future?5w@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BMP@FECG@There?5is?5much?5about?5the?5future?5w@ DB 'There is much'
	DB	' about the future we cannot see, but when it comes it will be'
	DB	' the children who wield it. The boy Wirt has a blackness upon'
	DB	' his soul, but he poses no threat to the town or its people. '
	DB	'His secretive dealings with the urchins and unspoken guilds o'
	DB	'f nearby towns gain him access to many devices that cannot be'
	DB	' easily found in Tristram. While his methods may be reproachf'
	DB	'ul, Wirt can provide assistance for your battle against the e'
	DB	'ncroaching Darkness. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0CAD@CBLM@Earthen?5walls?5and?5thatched?5canop@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0CAD@CBLM@Earthen?5walls?5and?5thatched?5canop@ DB 'Earthen walls a'
	DB	'nd thatched canopy do not a home create. The innkeeper Ogden '
	DB	'serves more of a purpose in this town than many understand. H'
	DB	'e provides shelter for Gillian and her matriarch, maintains w'
	DB	'hat life Farnham has left to him, and provides an anchor for '
	DB	'all who are left in the town to what Tristram once was. His t'
	DB	'avern, and the simple pleasures that can still be found there'
	DB	', provide a glimpse of a life that the people here remember. '
	DB	'It is that memory that continues to feed their hopes for your'
	DB	' success. |', 00H				; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
