_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0NH@EBOI@Not?5everyone?5in?5Tristram?5has?5a?5u@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0NH@EBOI@Not?5everyone?5in?5Tristram?5has?5a?5u@ DB 'Not everyone i'
	DB	'n Tristram has a use - or a market - for everything you will '
	DB	'find in the labyrinth. Not even me, as hard as that is to bel'
	DB	'ieve. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'Sometimes, only you will be able to '
	DB	'find a purpose for some things. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0GC@NCKB@Don?8t?5trust?5everything?5the?5drunk@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0GC@NCKB@Don?8t?5trust?5everything?5the?5drunk@ DB 'Don''t trust ev'
	DB	'erything the drunk says. Too many ales have fogged his vision'
	DB	' and his good sense. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0PK@MPPC@In?5case?5you?5haven?8t?5noticed?0?5I?5d@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0PK@MPPC@In?5case?5you?5haven?8t?5noticed?0?5I?5d@ DB 'In case you '
	DB	'haven''t noticed, I don''t buy anything from Tristram. I am a'
	DB	'n importer of quality goods. If you want to peddle junk, you'''
	DB	'll have to see Griswold, Pepin or that witch, Adria. I''m sur'
	DB	'e that they will snap up whatever you can bring them... |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBB@PNON@I?5guess?5I?5owe?5the?5blacksmith?5my?5@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBB@PNON@I?5guess?5I?5owe?5the?5blacksmith?5my?5@ DB 'I guess I ow'
	DB	'e the blacksmith my life - what there is of it. Sure, Griswol'
	DB	'd offered me an apprenticeship at the smithy, and he is a nic'
	DB	'e enough guy, but I''ll never get enough money to... well, le'
	DB	't''s just say that I have definite plans that require a large'
	DB	' amount of gold. |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBM@BDD@If?5I?5were?5a?5few?5years?5older?0?5I?5w@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBM@BDD@If?5I?5were?5a?5few?5years?5older?0?5I?5w@ DB 'If I were a'
	DB	' few years older, I would shower her with whatever riches I c'
	DB	'ould muster, and let me assure you I can get my hands on some'
	DB	' very nice stuff. Gillian is a beautiful girl who should get '
	DB	'out of Tristram as soon as it is safe. Hmmm... maybe I''ll ta'
	DB	'ke her with me when I go... |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0NM@EPHD@Cain?5knows?5too?5much?4?5He?5scares?5t@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0NM@EPHD@Cain?5knows?5too?5much?4?5He?5scares?5t@ DB 'Cain knows to'
	DB	'o much. He scares the life out of me - even more than that wo'
	DB	'man across the river. He keeps telling me about how lucky I a'
	DB	'm to be alive, and how my story is foretold in legend. I thin'
	DB	'k he''s off his crock. |', 00H		; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BGL@PMGC@Farnham?5?9?5now?5there?5is?5a?5man?5wit@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BGL@PMGC@Farnham?5?9?5now?5there?5is?5a?5man?5wit@ DB 'Farnham - n'
	DB	'ow there is a man with serious problems, and I know all about'
	DB	' how serious problems can be. He trusted too much in the inte'
	DB	'grity of one man, and Lazarus led him into the very jaws of d'
	DB	'eath. Oh, I know what it''s like down there, so don''t even s'
	DB	'tart telling me about your plans to destroy the evil that dwe'
	DB	'lls in that Labyrinth. Just watch your legs... |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0KE@KLJD@As?5long?5as?5you?5don?8t?5need?5anythi@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0KE@KLJD@As?5long?5as?5you?5don?8t?5need?5anythi@ DB 'As long as yo'
	DB	'u don''t need anything reattached, old Pepin is as good as th'
	DB	'ey come. ', 0aH, ' ', 0aH, 'If I''d have had some of those po'
	DB	'tions he brews, I might still have my leg... |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BDA@IAAA@Adria?5truly?5bothers?5me?4?5Sure?0?5Ca@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BDA@IAAA@Adria?5truly?5bothers?5me?4?5Sure?0?5Ca@ DB 'Adria truly '
	DB	'bothers me. Sure, Cain is creepy in what he can tell you abou'
	DB	't the past, but that witch can see into your past. She always'
	DB	' has some way to get whatever she needs, too. Adria gets her '
	DB	'hands on more merchandise than I''ve seen pass through the ga'
	DB	'tes of the King''s Bazaar during High Festival. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BBB@IGFO@Ogden?5is?5a?5fool?5for?5staying?5here@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BBB@IGFO@Ogden?5is?5a?5fool?5for?5staying?5here@ DB 'Ogden is a fo'
	DB	'ol for staying here. I could get him out of town for a very r'
	DB	'easonable price, but he insists on trying to make a go of it '
	DB	'with that stupid tavern. I guess at the least he gives Gillia'
	DB	'n a place to work, and his wife Garda does make a superb Shep'
	DB	'herd''s pie... |', 00H			; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0MD@OINA@Beyond?5the?5Hall?5of?5Heroes?5lies?5t@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0MD@OINA@Beyond?5the?5Hall?5of?5Heroes?5lies?5t@ DB 'Beyond the Hal'
	DB	'l of Heroes lies the Chamber of Bone. Eternal death awaits an'
	DB	'y who would seek to steal the treasures secured within this r'
	DB	'oom. So speaks the Lord of Terror, and so it is written. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0HL@PJLJ@?4?4?4and?5so?0?5locked?5beyond?5the?5Gat@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0HL@PJLJ@?4?4?4and?5so?0?5locked?5beyond?5the?5Gat@ DB '...and so, '
	DB	'locked beyond the Gateway of Blood and past the Hall of Fire,'
	DB	' Valor awaits for the Hero of Light to awaken... |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BAA@NLCC@I?5can?5see?5what?5you?5see?5not?4?6Visi@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BAA@NLCC@I?5can?5see?5what?5you?5see?5not?4?6Visi@ DB 'I can see w'
	DB	'hat you see not.', 0aH, 'Vision milky then eyes rot.', 0aH, 'W'
	DB	'hen you turn they will be gone,', 0aH, 'Whispering their hidd'
	DB	'en song.', 0aH, 'Then you see what cannot be,', 0aH, 'Shadows'
	DB	' move where light should be.', 0aH, 'Out of darkness, out of '
	DB	'mind,', 0aH, 'Cast down into the Halls of the Blind. |', 0aH, 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0OJ@FKCI@The?5armories?5of?5Hell?5are?5home?5to@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0OJ@FKCI@The?5armories?5of?5Hell?5are?5home?5to@ DB 'The armories o'
	DB	'f Hell are home to the Warlord of Blood. In his wake lay the '
	DB	'mutilated bodies of thousands. Angels and man alike have been'
	DB	' cut down to fulfill his endless sacrifices to the Dark ones '
	DB	'who scream for one thing - blood. |', 00H	; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BPE@JMJL@Take?5heed?5and?5bear?5witness?5to?5th@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BPE@JMJL@Take?5heed?5and?5bear?5witness?5to?5th@ DB 'Take heed and'
	DB	' bear witness to the truths that lie herein, for they are the'
	DB	' last legacy of the Horadrim. There is a war that rages on ev'
	DB	'en now, beyond the fields that we know - between the utopian '
	DB	'kingdoms of the High Heavens and the chaotic pits of the Burn'
	DB	'ing Hells. This war is known as the Great Conflict, and it ha'
	DB	's raged and burned longer than any of the stars in the sky. N'
	DB	'either side ever gains sway for long as the forces of Light a'
	DB	'nd Darkness constantly vie for control over all creation. |', 00H ; `string'
_DATA	ENDS
;	COMDAT ??_C@_0BNB@LDEK@Take?5heed?5and?5bear?5witness?5to?5th@
_DATA	SEGMENT
??_C@_0BNB@LDEK@Take?5heed?5and?5bear?5witness?5to?5th@ DB 'Take heed and'
	DB	' bear witness to the truths that lie herein, for they are the'
	DB	' last legacy of the Horadrim. When the Eternal Conflict betwe'
	DB	'en the High Heavens and the Burning Hells falls upon mortal s'
	DB	'oil, it is called the Sin War. Angels and Demons walk amongst'
	DB	' humanity in disguise, fighting in secret, away from the pryi'
	DB	'ng eyes of mortals. Some daring, powerful mortals have even a'
	DB	'llied themselves with either side, and helped to dictate the '
